  |                                                                         |
  |     Summary                                                             |
  |   -------------------------------------------------------------------   |
  |                                                                         |
  |   'Energy Cycle Edge' is the sequel to the puzzle game 'Energy          |
  |   Cycle'.                                                               |
  |                                                                         |
  |   The main idea is the same: when you activate each cell in the game    |
  |   field, it changes the colors of the cell and any adjacent cells in    |
  |   a straight line. Each cell switches between three different colors,   |
  |   and your task is to make them all match the same color.               |
  |                                                                         |
  |   In 'Energy Cycle Edge', most part of puzzles are three-dimensional,   |
  |   so you'll need to monitor the changes of colors within several        |
  |   linked layers, adding a new facet to the familiar gameplay.           |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * 44 levels in 4 different sets                                       |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * IDM/Ambient soundtrack from different artists                       |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * «Random colors» mode that allows you to go through any level        |
  |     multiple times                                                      |
  |                                                                         |
  |   * «Classic cells» mode for fans of the original game                  |
  |                                                                         |
  |   Languages: English, French, Italian, German, Spanish, Portuguese,     |
  |   Dutch, Hungarian, Russian, Greek, Polish, Romanian, Turkish,          |
  |   Suomi (Finnish), Bulgarian, Danish, Norwegian, Thai, Swedish,         |
  |   Czech, Arabic, Japanese, Korean and Simplified Chinese.               |
